# GuideMill — Project Development Summary
_March 29, 2026 (updated)_

---

## What Is GuideMill?
GuideMill is a CNC-style guided milling machine. A Raspberry Pi hosts the user interface (PyQt5); an ESP32-S3 handles real-time motion control, optical sensing, and motor actuation. The two communicate over a one-byte serial protocol via UART (USB/ACM).

---

## Architecture

```
Raspberry Pi  <--UART/USB-->  ESP32-S3 devkit C1 N16R8
 PyQt5 GUI                     PlatformIO / Arduino-ESP32
 mcuCom.py                     Usart class (io/usart.cpp)
 McuCheckThread                sensors / actuation
```

- **Sensors**: PMW3360 optical flow, SPI bus (SS0=GPIO3 wired; SS1-SS3 not yet connected)
- **Motors**: TMC2209 stepper drivers (L/R/Z), UART-addressed on Serial1 (RX=18, TX=5, EN=40)
- **Firmware serial**: UART0, PIN_RX=44, PIN_TX=43, 115200 baud

---

## Serial Protocol (one-byte)

| Byte   | Direction    | Meaning                              |
|--------|--------------|--------------------------------------|
| `0xA5` | Pi → ESP32   | REQUEST_ACK — ping                        |
| `0x5A` | ESP32 → Pi   | RESPONSE_ACK — pong                       |
| `0xB0` | Pi → ESP32   | REQUEST_TEST_SENSORS                      |
| `0xB1` | Pi → ESP32   | REQUEST_TEST_MOTORS                       |
| `0x1X` | ESP32 → Pi   | Sensor result (low nibble = failmask)     |
| `0x2X` | ESP32 → Pi   | Motor result  (low nibble = failmask)     |
| `0xC0` | Pi → ESP32   | REQUEST_HOME_XY — home XY (blocking)      |
| `0xC1` | Pi → ESP32   | REQUEST_MOTORS_HOMED — query homed state  |
| `0xC5` | ESP32 → Pi   | RESPONSE_HOME_DONE — homing complete      |
| `0xC6` | ESP32 → Pi   | RESPONSE_HOMED — motors are homed         |
| `0xC7` | ESP32 → Pi   | RESPONSE_NOT_HOMED — motors not homed     |

Failmask bits: sensors bit0=S0..bit3=S3; motors bit0=L, bit1=R, bit2=Z.

---

## Key Scripts

| Script | Location | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `build_and_flash.sh` | `GuideMill-ESP32/scripts/` | Build firmware (PlatformIO) → scp binaries → flash on Pi |
| `flash.sh` | Pi: `~/GuideMill-flash/` | Flash all three bins at correct addresses (0x0, 0x8000, 0x10000) |
| `test-esp-com.sh` | `GuideMill-ESP32/scripts/` | Copy test script to Pi and run interactively |
| `test-com.py` | `GuideMill-ESP32/src/test_esp/` | Interactive ACK loop tester over `/dev/ttyACM0` |
| `sync-to-pi.sh` | `pi/scripts/` | rsync `pi/` to Pi, clear `__pycache__`, launch GUI |
| `test-gui.sh` | Pi: `~/uis/scripts/` | Generate Win.py files, run `src/main.py` |

---

## Recent Firmware Work (GuideMill-ESP32/)

- **`src/usart.h`** — protocol constants (all commands + responses)
- **`src/io/usart.cpp`** — `Usart` class: `begin()`, `update()`, `handleByte()` dispatch
- **`src/sensors/sensors.cpp`** — `sensorSetup()`, `checkSensors()` (SPI, PMW3360 init, bitmask)
- **`src/actuation/motors.cpp`** — `driverSetup()`, `pingDriver()` (TPWMTHRS roundtrip), `checkDrivers()`; `disableStepperRL()` and `disableStepperZ()` now reset `motorsHomed = false`
- **`src/globals.h/cpp`** — added `bool motorsHomed` (default `false`); set to `true` after successful homing
- **`src/main.cpp`** — minimal entry point: `usart.begin()` / `usart.update()`

---

## Recent Pi GUI Work (pi/)

- **`src/mcuCom.py`** — `find_mcu_port()` scans `/dev/serial/by-id`, ttyUSB*, ttyACM*; `check_mcu_present()` does handshake
- **`src/main.py`** — `McuCheckThread(QThread)` runs MCU check off main thread; `cbMCU` checkbox turns green/orange/red based on result
- **`src/appSettings.py`** — fixed pydantic v2 import (`pydantic_settings`)

